rest_of_day_open: I see it being a very painful remainder of the week. I have some issues with my mother in law who is also my lead, and I have to work with her Wednesday and Thursday this week, and I'm more anxious/nervous/scared than I've ever been in my life, because she's almost a bully of sorts.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is that we were both open minded and willing to listen to one another's opinions/ideas.  I think it was beneficial that we both went into it with our ears open, and were willing to hear what the other person had to say without holding any sort of bias or preconceived opinions about each other.
critical_negative: I think we had a hard time letting one another take a turn to speak, or know when the other person was ready to talk. We kind of spoke over each other on a few occasions cause we weren't sure if the other was about to initiate conversation or not.

rest_of_day_open: It will be okay. It's not slated to be very eventful. I'll just have the opportunity to sit back and relax. Hopefully I can enjoy some cooking and exercising. One medical appointment, not really anything to worry about. I want to take the time to improve myself as much as possible and maybe clean.
critical_positive: We were both from rural areas. We both sympathize with both the police and plight of African-Americans--with all people. We think covid should be taken seriously, but handled correctly and politely by officials. We both were interested to hear from people of different experiences. We come from messy houses which was good for a laugh.
critical_negative: I kept stumbling over my words. Perhaps I revealed too much about myself. I replaced one word with another too frequently. A train passed by on my end obscuring vocal communication for about two minutes. I was very embarrassed about this. My place is too messy for video conversations. There might have been a glare.
